{
  "local_port": 44550,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you cook cube steak?",
  "response": "Cube steak, also known as cubed steak, is a tenderized cut of beef that can be delicious and flavorful if cooked properly. Here are a few methods to cook cube steak:\n\n### Pan-Frying\n1. **Ingredients:**\n   - Cube steaks\n   - Salt and pepper to taste\n   - Flour (optional)\n   - Oil (vegetable, canola, or olive)\n   - Butter (optional)\n   - Garlic powder or any preferred seasoning (optional)\n\n2. **Instructions:**\n   1. **Season the Steaks:** Season the cube steaks with salt, pepper, and any additional spices you prefer. If desired, lightly dredge them in flour for a nice crust.\n   2. **Heat the Pan:** Add a couple of tablespoons of oil or a combination of oil and butter to a large skillet over medium-high heat.\n   3. **Cook the Steaks:** Once the oil is hot, place the cube steaks in the skillet. Allow them to cook for about 3-4 minutes on each side until they are nicely browned and cooked through.\n   4. **Rest:** Remove the steaks from the skillet and let them rest for a few minutes before serving.\n\n### Gravy Preparation (Optional):\n1. **Ingredients:**\n   - Drippings from the skillet\n   - Flour (if not already used)\n   - Beef broth\n   - Salt and pepper to taste\n   - Milk or cream (optional)\n\n2. **Instructions:**\n   1. **Making the Roux:** If you have leftover drippings, sprinkle a couple of tablespoons of flour in the skillet and stir to combine with the drippings. Cook for a minute or two.\n   2. **Adding Liquids:** Gradually add beef broth to the mixture, stirring continuously to avoid lumps. Add enough broth to achieve your preferred gravy thickness.\n   3. **Seasoning and Finishing:** Season the gravy with salt and pepper. You can also add a splash of milk or cream for a richer flavor. Simmer until the gravy thickens to your liking.\n\n### Baking\n1. **Ingredients:**\n   - Cube steaks\n   - Salt and pepper to taste\n   - Beef broth or mushroom soup\n   - Sliced onions (optional)\n   - Sliced mushrooms (optional)\n\n2. **Instructions:**\n   1. **Preheat Oven:** Preheat your oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C).\n   2. **Prepare the Dish:** Season the cube steaks and place them in a baking dish. Pour beef broth or mushroom soup over the steaks. You can add sliced onions and mushrooms for extra flavor.\n   3. **Bake:** Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for about 1 to 1.5 hours until the steak is tender.\n   4. **Serve:** Once done, serve the cube steak with the gravy from the baking dish.\n\n### Slow Cooking\n1. **Ingredients:**\n   - Cube steaks\n   - Salt and pepper to taste\n   - Beef broth or tomato sauce\n   - Sliced onions (optional)\n   - Sliced mushrooms (optional)\n\n2. **Instructions:**\n   1. **Prepare the Cube Steaks:** Season the cube steaks.\n   2. **Slow Cooker:** Place the cube steaks in the slow cooker and pour beef broth or tomato sauce over them. Add sliced onions and mushrooms if desired.\n   3. **Cook:** Set the slow cooker to low and cook for 6-8 hours or until the meat is tender and flavorful.\n   4. **Serve:** Serve the cube steak with the rich sauce from the slow cooker.\n\nCube steak pairs well with mashed potatoes, steamed vegetables, or rice. Enjoy your meal!",
